metadata.name: Syzers #549
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

···· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ····

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template.

metadata.name: Haemo Globs #240
metadata.description:
The shape and function of haematids (red blood cells) has always fascinated me. Perhaps their mathematical smoothness and candy-like aspect resonated with me as a child. Their simple appearance distinguished them from the other cell types I had learned about. I imagined them engorged with sweet-flavoured oxygen and juicily popping under my bite.

I hope for this generative artwork to communicate my appreciation for these never-ending body travellers.

objkt.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #98

metadata.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #98
metadata.description:
Experimental generative collection that merges analog photography, AI, generative text, and algorithmic coding, by digging down into the essence and building blocks of the different artistic communication channels. 

This work engages with all aforementioned mediums in a joint manner, guided by a random process. It starts with a collection of analog photographs, shot on film and scanned that were later used as a training dataset in Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) training. This way, A.I. learns the main characteristics of film photography. In particular, it mimics its recognizable grain. Another type of pixel grain is added with the use of code and pixel shifting as well as digital manipulation. Finally, the last type of “grain” appears with the use of generative text where a different kind of A.I. was given a short description of the project and instructed to imagine the rest of the story. The fragmented and void of meaning parts of generative text are added to the images as one of the possible traits.

issuer.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I.
